        "timing": "Occurred after death",
        "description": "A central part of funerary rites, where the deceased's heart was weighed against Ma'at's feather. If the heart was lighter or equal, the person was deemed worthy of entering the afterlife. This ceremony emphasized the importance of living a life aligned with truth and justice."
